@10101  = ~You'll have to excuse me, everything is a mess, with Thalantyr gone. I am managing things until his return.~
@10102  = ~Where has he gone?~
@10103  = ~Oh, he has not gone anywhere. He is dead. Killed! Just last night! Oh, if only I was here, I... well, I imagine I would also now be dead. Anyone who can take out Master Thalantyr must be dangerous indeed.~
@10104  = ~And whoever it was, they took those thrice-damned Netherese bracers!~
@10105  = ~That sounds bad. But why did you say 'when he returns?' Is he to be resurrected?~
@10106  = ~Oh no, no, he does not approve of the use of clerical magic. He has made his own contingent arrangements in case of his demise. Some kind of combination of reincarnation and regeneration, if I understand it correctly. The process should be complete in a few weeks? Maybe? I'm afraid it's a bit over my head - I'm just his apprentice! ...I have really learned to appreciate my limits, lately.~
@10107  = ~Right. Would you be willing to buy or sell items from Thalantyr's stock?~
@10108  = ~Ah. Well, I suppose he would not mind if I conducted some business on his behalf. He has trained me well in balancing the tower's accounts, if not in the actual use of magic.~
@10109  = ~Great. Let's see what you have for sale.~
@10110  = ~Ah. Well, best of luck then. We must get on with our business.~
@10111  = ~And at last, we have the bracers! Now I will make quite sure to store these a bit more securely. And at length I will determine a method to destroy them, or at least permanently disable them. Thank you for your assistance in this matter.~
@10112  = ~You are welcome.~
@10113  = ~You are welcome. May we peruse your inventory of magical items?~
@10114  = ~I hope those halflings appreciate the effort I put into this...~
@10115  = ~Yes, yes, boy, now be quiet a moment. Ah ha, here they are. Now to make certain these will not fall into the hands of some other unfortunate fool. I will store them securely, this time. Tell me, Melicamp, do you quite feel yourself again?~
//
//
@10200  = ~The Hunt for Sarevok~
@10201  = ~Well. I suppose we must thank you for your timely intervention. Though, if I am being honest, the timing of your arrival does seem quite convenient. Who did you say you are?~
@10202  = ~I am <CHARNAME>. We have been investigating the Iron Throne's involvement with the iron crisis and the push for war with Amn. We have spoken to Scar about it.~
@10203  = ~Yes, well, unfortunately Scar is dead, and won't be coming back. So we cannot ask him about it.~
@10204  = ~At any rate, Sarevok is gone, and there is no way to track where they went. That was a Dimension Door, not a teleport spell. But the range is limited, so he cannot have gone far. He is surely still in the city. I will order all entrances to be monitored and have mages checking for magical passage. He will not easily escape.~
@10205  = ~You assume he *wants* to escape...~
@10206  = ~He will wish he could escape. I will hunt him down!~
@10207  = ~Yes, he did say he would come after you right before leaving, did he not? That is worrying. With all the power he amassed through the Iron Throne, he no doubt still has significant resources close at hand.~
@10208  = ~I admire your enthusiasm. It is clear to me that Sarevok is an enemy who meant to cause - who did cause - grave harm. But you might consider whether, in your zeal to pursue him, you are playing into his hands. With all the power he amassed through the Iron Throne, he no doubt still has significant resources close at hand.~
@10209  = ~We must find him. I think the best course of action is to inquire with the Flaming Fist. Sarevok's stooge, Angelo, is gone and his goons will have been run out. But maybe someone gleaned some information from him in the short time he was running the place.~
@10210  = ~Good idea. I will go talk to an officer in the Flaming Fist.~
@10211  = ~I do not really see eye to eye with the Flaming Fist. I suppose I could talk to them... if I feel like it. We'll see.~
@10212  = ~I urge you to find Sarevok and bring him to justice. It would be a boon for the city... and it would go a long way toward shoring up your own credibility and reputation.~
@10213  = ~Right. I am on it.~
@10214  = ~I do what I want to do, you aren't my boss.~
@10215  = ~Can I help you? I'm afraid we don't have the time for civilian inquiries at the moment.~
@10216  = ~Say, I know you. You're that troublemaker that Angelo wanted us to arrest!~
@10217  = ~Heh heh. Well, an enemy of Angelo's is a friend of mine. That guy was no good for the Fist. What can I do for you?~
@10218  = ~I am trying to track down Sarevok Anchev. He was working with Angelo and I need to put a stop to their scheming, once and for all. Do you have any information about where they might be?~
@10219  = ~Nothing right now. I have to do some things, then maybe I will be back.~
@10220  = ~I can't say that I do. I'm sorry. However... Sarevok and Angelo didn't exactly hide their activities. Why should they? A grand duke and the leader of the Flaming fist!~
@10221  = ~When Sarevok was angling to become a duke, he was courting favor with most of the city's noble families. Some were more eager than others to work with him. One in particular, name of Korlasz, seemed unusually eager to get involved. Well, I asked around a bit - quiet, like - and rumor has it she is into some dark magicks.~
@10222  = ~Do you think Korlasz might have information on where Sarevok and Angelo are now? Where is her estate?~
@10223  = ~Funny thing, that. I already sent some men 'round to her house. But nobody was home. And nobody has come or gone in some time. But, here's where it gets interesting. There was one time, when Angelo met with this Korlasz, and he ordered a squad of Fist men to accompany him for protection. But they didn't go to her house. See, Korlasz also has a big fancy crypt for her family, right in the middle of the city. And that's where the meet took place.~
@10224  = ~Now, I have to ask myself: why would they want to hold a meeting in a bleedin' mausoleum? It's a head-scratcher, hey? But I tell you what: I would like to see this mausoleum. I would like that very much. Who knows? Maybe we will find Angelo there. I would quite like to see him strapped to a hard chair in the basement, and answer some questions for me.~
@10225  = ~I would like that as well. Can you tell me where this crypt is? It's all I have to go on.~
@10226  = ~Tell me where the crypt is. You stay here - you will only get in my way.~
@10227  = ~It is right near the center of the city, north of the harbor near the steps to the entrance in the old walls. I am already gathering a force to go there and get inside, by force if necessary. I was there that night and I saw how to bypass the wards at the entrance. My men are heading there soon; if you want to join, you can meet me there. I won't lie, I wouldn't mind having someone with your capabilities along with my men.~
@10228  = ~Sounds good.~
@10229  = ~I've got some things to do first. I will meet you there afterward.~
@10230  = ~Sorry friend, but I'm not sitting this one out. Anyway, you can't get past the wards without me. So if you want in, you can meet me there. The crypt is right near the center of the city, north of the harbor near the steps to the entrance in the old walls. I won't lie, I wouldn't mind having someone with your... capabilities... along with my men. If things get violent, though, you make sure those weapons of yours are pointed in the right direction. Understand?~
@10231  = ~Fine, I will meet you there. But your men better not slow me down.~
@10232  = ~No promises.~
@10233  = ~Alright then, I will see you there.~
@10234  = ~The Hunt for Sarevok
I spoke with Captain Gregson of the Flaming Fist. He did not know where Sarevok and Angelo may be, but he mentioned a member of the noble class, Korlasz, who had some suspicious dealings with Angelo at her family's crypt in the center of the city. Captain Gregson intends to enter the crypt and look for clues. It is as good a place to start as any. The entrance to the crypt is near the gate in the inner city walls, just north of the harbor. Captain Gregson will meet me there with a company of Flaming Fist soldiers.~
@10235  = ~The Hunt for Sarevok
Sarevok's coronation as a grand duke was interrupted, but he escaped to an unknown location. The dukes have suggested that an officer of the Flaming Fist who may have worked with Angelo might have information that can help. Angelo was installed, however briefly, at the Flaming Fist headquarters ion the southwest quadrant of the city. That is the best place to start.~
@10236  = ~The Hunt for Sarevok~
//
//
@10301  = ~It's good you are here! My scouts tell me that Korlasz is inside the crypt right now! We do not know whether Sarevok or Angelo is with her, however.~
@10302  = ~The bad news is, I'm afraid they saw us mustering outside - one of my men heard them raise an alarm and they retreated further into the crypt. We have entered the antechamber, and apparently it opens into a rather large cave complex. We do not know how large, or where it leads. My guess is, either there is another way out, or they are fortifying and making ready for a tough fight. I don't know which possibility I prefer...~
@10303  = ~We may be facing a tough fight in there. Let me know when you are ready to proceed.~
@10304  = ~I need to take care of a couple things first. I will return when I am prepared to go after Korlasz.~
@10305  = ~I am ready now. Let's go in.~
@10306  = ~Alright, my men will guard the entrance until you are ready to go in. We will make sure no one gets in or out.~
@10307  = ~You are back. Are you ready to go into the crypt to pursue Korlasz?~
@10308  = ~A small force of Sarevok's followers are further in - mostly mercenaries and former Iron Throne die-hards. They are presumably with Korlasz. Careful with her, she is a necromancer. Expect resistance, and expect traps. And above all, expect undead. I will stay here and secure the exit. Good luck.~
@10309  = ~Is everything going okay? There is a Flaming Fist healer inside the crypt if you need assistance. We should make sure Korlasz does not have a chance to get away.~
@10310  = ~Great work in there. I need to get back to the Flaming Fist to get started on the paperwork. But you are the hero of the hour. You should return to the Ducal Palace and report our success here.~
@10311  = ~Everything's a mess. We should have gotten out of the city days ago.~
@10312  = ~This chamber is secure. We can proceed when you're ready.~
@10313  = ~You're too late. They've already gone.~
@10314  = ~Aren't you here for... I thought...~
@10315  = ~Sarevok paid us well, but something tells me he is not long for this world, and I am in no rush to die. Everyone, lay down your arms.~
@10316  = ~But you do, <CHARNAME>. Destroy <PRO_HIMHER>!~
@10317  = ~I... am defeated.~
@10320  = ~[Message from Sarevok to Korlasz]Korlasz, as you have no doubt heard, my coronation as grand duke was interrupted. We must regroup - all is not yet lost. I may have been denied my war, but with proper preparations the death of <CHARNAME> will still empower me. <PRO_HESHE> will no doubt be coming to confront me - <PRO_HESHE> cannot afford not to. But we will be ready. Collect what resources you can and meet me at the temple in the Undercity.

Sarevok~
@10321  = ~The Hunt for Sarevok
Korlasz is dead. She refused to surrender, fighting to the end for Sarevok. I should search for any clues to his whereabouts.~
@10322  = ~The Hunt for Sarevok
Korlasz has surrendered to the Flaming Fist. Whether she will willingly betray Sarevok is another question, however. I should search the area for any clues to his whereabouts.~
@10323  = ~The Hunt for Sarevok
I discovered a letter from Sarevok among Korlasz' things. It appears to have been hastily written, and mentions that he is calling for his supporters and allies to meet him in the Undercity. He appears to be preparing for a final confrontation. Dukes Belt and Liia will likely have an idea of how to find the Undercity.~
@10324  = ~The name craftfully caved into ornamented flagstones identifies this as the Korlasz family crypt entrance. It is well closed and magically protected.~
//
//
@10401  = ~You have returned! A Flaming Fist messenger has informed us of your success.~
@10402  = ~It is a shame that Korlasz felt she had to die. I wonder that a knave like Sarevok can engender such stubborn loyalty...~
@10403  = ~Korlasz is in custody. She is, for now, refusing to tell us anything about Sarevok. I wonder that a knave like Sarevok can engender such stubborn loyalty...~
@10404  = ~Tell me, did you find any information about Sarevok or his whereabouts?~
@10405  = ~We have found nothing useful.~
@10406  = ~We found a letter from Sarevok to Korlasz. It mentions an Undercity? A place inside Baldur's Gate? Do you know what he is talking about?~
@10407  = ~Well, you should make sure you scour the crypt, it is our best lead at the moment. Korlasz is an important ally of Sarevok, she is sure to have some information.~
@10408  = ~Liia is the history expert here, I will defer to her on this.~
@10409  = ~Ah yes. The city's history is quite old. Older than the bricks of these buildings, older than Balduran. There have been rumors that the decaying remains of the original city still lie somewhere beneath us.~
@10410  = ~Of course the rumors also say the old city is exceedingly dangerous. Who knows what evils might be buried down there? The truth is, as dukes of the city we have a responsibility to protect our citizens from dangers below. So, we were told that our predecessors magically warded any known passages. And, being unusable, they were mostly forgotten.~
@10411  = ~I don't know what passage Sarevok found, or how he bypassed the wards. Maybe he found a route nobody ever knew about. I can only guess that he has found some source of power there - that could explain his extraordinary success in his schemes. In my lifetime, the only rumors I have heard of such things is of a blocked-off area in the thieves' guild, inaccessible even to its own members. That certainly conforms to the stories of those ancient warrens.~
@10412  = ~We dare not send troops in force - Angelo was quite cruel in dealing with the guild, and it has created a volatile situation. I fear reprisals if we were to send Flaming Fist soldiers into the heart of their domain. Especially given the rumors from the north, it is important to promote unity and normalcy, not risk further strife. Better that an independent agent investigate the rumored passage. Here, I will apply a magical rune on your hand. Sort of a 'key to the city.' If you can find a way to the Undercity, this tattoo will allow you to traverse it.~
@10413  = ~~
@10414  = ~~
@10415  = ~The Hunt for Sarevok
I have discovered a staircase inside the Thieves' Guild which leads underground. The Past it is an old maze. From the corridors I can hear the sounds of shuffling bones and shifting slimes. I should be on guard - wherever this path leads, it is clearly not meant to be easy to reach.~
@10416  = ~~
@10417  = ~What? Daddy no! You don't understand - <CHARNAME> is my friend. <PRO_HESHE> has been with me. There's no way <PRO_HESHE> could have killed you we were nowhere near the estate.~
@10418  = ~Is... is this true? Did you murder my dad? Wait, when could that even have happened?~
@10419  = ~What is going on here??~
@10420  = ~What in the Abyss is going on here?? Do you know who you are talking to?~
@10421  = ~Duke Silvershield! You're back! How are you feeling?~
@10422  = ~Never mind that! I want to know what this person is doing here in the palace, unguarded!~
@10423  = ~<CHARNAME>? <PRO_HESHE> just returned from a mission for us- ~
@10424  = ~A mission?! For you? How are you letting this happen? Don't you understand - <CHARNAME> murdered me!~
@10425  = ~Entar, you have been... er, away, these recent days. You are not aware of the threat: doppelgangers, posing as citizens, were infiltrating parts of the city. It was all part of Sarevok's plan. The iron crisis, the bandit raids, the Seven Suns and the Iron Throne - it was Sarevok all along.~
@10426  = ~Nonsense! Do you think a slimy hissing doppelganger could kill me?~
@10427  = ~Entar... they killed a lot of people. Listen, you are not fully caught up on the situation. Resurrection takes a lot out of you. And this isn't your first. You need rest. The situation here is in hand. We have a lead on Sarevok's whereabouts. <CHARNAME> is going to find him, and report back to use so we can send the Flaming Fist to bring him to justice. Once he is in our custody, all will be made clear. Now please, go rest.~
@10428  = ~Yes, indeed, all will be made very clear. I tell you, that was no doppelganger. I know what I saw. This is not over!~
@10429  = ~Entar, please. You are back with us. Duke Eltan is on the mend. Emissaries have already been dispatched to sue for peace with Amn. The threat to the city has been eliminated - thanks in no small part to <CHARNAME>. Now please, get some rest.~
@10430  = ~This is not over!~
@10431  = ~I apologize for that outburst. Do not worry, he will come around. While his accusation is disturbing, I am sure our explanation is the correct one. What else would it be? For now, please focus on the task at hand: it is imperative that Sarevok be found, and brought to justice. Do not confront him if you can help it. Let us know his location and we can arrange for a squadron of Flaming Fist soldiers to accompany you to detain him. We want him back here alive, if possible. But, even if dead, we can work with that. Just be sure to bring his body back here, so we can resurrect him, or in the worst case just commune with his spirit.~
@10432  = ~You can prove Entar wrong, and show your loyalty to the city, by getting this task done.~
@10433  = ~Please do not delay in finding Sarevok, and if you cannot avoid a fight, remember to bring his body back here.~
@10434  = ~Duke Silvershield's Accusation
Duke Entar Silvershield was resurrected and has returned to the Ducal Palace after having been murdered by agents of Sarevok. He appeared quite out of sorts, making angry accusations that *I* had murdered him. That of course is not possible, and the doppelganger situation was explained to him. Still, he seems adamant that his attacker was no doppelganger. I cannot say why he is so sure. Maybe after he has rested and fully recovered, he will see reason.~
@10435  = ~The Hunt for Sarevok
Duke Liia Jannath has given me a clue to where to look for the Undercity. She mentioned passages underground which were specially warded long ago, but apparently the dukes have the power to bypass those wards. She inscribed a rune on my hand, in case I find such a passage. I have been directed to investigate the rumor of an old disused passage to the Undercity inside the Baldur's Gate Thieves' Guild. The dukes asked that I not confront Sarevok, directly, but only find his location and report back so they can send reinforcements. The situation still seems volatile...~
@10436  = ~~
@10437  = ~~
@10438  = ~~
@10439  = ~Imoen's Return
I have not seen Imoen in some time, but she has apparently made her own way to the Ducal Palace and befriended Duke Liia Jannath. Duke Liia seems interested in helping Imoen discover her full potential. While I search out Sarevok to put an end to his schemes at last, Imoen will stay at the palace under the dukes' protection.~
@10440  = ~Heya! It's me, Imoen!~
@10441  = ~Before you go, <CHARNAME>, a small surprise. An old companion of yours would like to say hello.~
@10442  = ~Heya <CHARNAME>! It's been a while. I hear you've been having lots of adventures, without me. That's fine. Really! They sound like amazing fun. Anyway, I've had a bit of a journey myself. I was back at Candlekeep, you know, and there was some real creepy stuff going on there. People changing faces. Most of the monks are so clueless, they had no idea. But I did! Only, I didn't really know what to do about it. And then I heard you were back! But you got arrested before I could see you. That wasn't very smart of you!~
@10443  = ~Heya <CHARNAME>! It's been a while. I hear you've been having lots of adventures, without me. That's fine. Really! I hung around Beregost and the Friendly Arm Inn for a while - Bentley has some really great stories, from when he was an adventurer. Only, I got bored pretty quick, you know? So, once news reached us of the murders at Candlekeep, I figured you probably got yourself into trouble and needed me to come help! It wasn't hard to see that the Iron Throne was probably at the heart of everything that was going on, so you would probably come to the city.~
@10444  = ~Heya <CHARNAME>! Have you taken down Sarevok yet, or what? Heh, just jokin'. I've been, you know, hanging around the city. Got kind of bored, to be honest. But then I met this halfling, and she can get into all kinds of places, and - er, maybe we shouldn't talk about that here. I'll tell you more about it later, I guess.~
@10445  = ~Heya <CHARNAME>! It's me! I was dead. I mean, mostly dead? I'm not *exactly* sure what happened, but I remember this nice cleric was talking to me, said he was a miracle worker (I think that means cleric) and he said there's a big difference between mostly dead and all dead, and I guess I was just mostly dead. It sounds a bit weird to me, but, here I am!~
@10446  = ~~
@10447  = ~Anyway, I eventually heard about the doppelganger attack at the coronation, and tracked you down here! And that's how I met Duke Liia. She's super nice!~
@10448  = ~Imoen here is a very interesting young woman. It has been enjoyable getting to know her. She told me all about how you both came to be raised in Candlekeep. I believe that beyond her childlike exuberance is an unusually sharp mind.~
@10449  = ~Duke Liia says she thinks I can do magic! I mean, not just do it, but that I could be really good at it!~
@10450  = ~We shall see. There is certainly a depth of... potential in you that most cannot see. I think I would very much like to explore that together. In the meantime, I think it is best that close associates of <CHARNAME> stay here with us, under the watch of our guards. Until the machinations of Sarevok are well and truly ended, we would do well to keep Imoen secure.~
@10451  = ~We are going after Sarevok now. Imoen, why don't you join me, and help me take him down for good?~
@10452  = ~That makes sense.~
@10453  = ~Whatever. Imoen is not my concern.~
@10454  = ~Aw, I really want to! I would love to give him a good smack when he's not looking. But Liia thinks it would be a bad idea. Something about 'not committing all one's resources in times of chaos.' I dunno, it made sense at the time. Anyway, she's teaching me magic, and Liia is, like, the BEST at magic. Just think how much stronger I'll be once I'm properly instructed!~
@10455  = ~There are many moving parts here. You have your mission, and Imoen has hers. Once you know Sarevok's location, we can discuss the matter further. Now go with haste, please. It would not do well to allow Sarevok to spend too much time fortifying whatever hole he has fled to.~
@10456  = ~Heya. Do you believe this place? Liia gave me a room of my own. It's WAY nicer than anything in Candlekeep. The food's a lot better too. ...I really wanted to be traveling with you these past days. But, it's okay, I don't hold it against you. Liia says I've got to walk my own path for a while, and I think I agree with her. Good luck with Sarevok!~
@10457  = ~Thanks Imoen. I'm glad you are okay. Don't get into too much trouble here in the palace, okay?~
@10458  = ~Oh, don't worry, I'll get into just the right amount of trouble. I'm an expert.~
@10459  = ~I can't believe you aren't coming along to help.~
@10460  = ~Didn't you hear me, ya bufflehead? Not everything is about you!~
@10461  = ~You got him! Great job! Now maybe things can get back to normal.~
@10462  = ~~
@10463  = ~Here now, who are you?? I warn you we have very little tolerance for trespassers at the moment!~
@10464  = ~Well, I have little tolerance for thieves who get in my way. Draw steel!~
@10465  = ~Don't worry, we are not here to attack you. This might sound odd but, is there are area here that you cannot access?~
@10466  = ~Well. That is an odd question. And I have an odder answer, because I think there might be such a place.~
@10467  = ~Sometimes, especially when I have a Potion of Perception in my system, out of the corner of my eye, I have the most fleeting idea that I saw something over there. A staircase, maybe? But then I look, and of course there is nothing. Just a trick of the light, for sure.~
@10468  = ~What, you mean that staircase?~
@10469  = ~What staircase.~
@10470  = ~That staircase right there.~
@10471  = ~Friend, I have no idea what you are talking... wait. Are you telling me you see a staircase there?~
@10472  = ~Yes, right there, a staircase going down into the basement. It must be the one you just mentioned.~
@10473  = ~Well this is getting odder and odder, friend, because this building has no basement. There is naught beneath our feet but earth. The sewers don't even reach this corner of the city.~
@10474  = ~I plainly see stairs going down. And if it is all the same to you, I am going to go down there.~
@10475  = ~Go down th... you know what, you are acting very weird, and I just don't have time for it right now. If you don't start making sense then I am going to insist you leave.~
@10476  = ~By Helm's bollocks! Where were you off to just then?? I saw you here with me, and then you were nowhere at all. But no trace of teleporting or dimension-dooring! And you weren't invisible neither - I felt all around for you! Felt reeeal hard. Mask perserve us, that's a neat trick! I don't... eh... don't suppose you can teach it to me, could you?~
@10477  = ~~
@10478  = ~<CHARNAME>, if I might delay you for a moment? I would like to speak with Imoen.~
@10479  = ~Yes, child. I have been observing you. Your mind is quite adept - moreso than you let on. Whether it be a difficult lock or learning a new bit of magic, you have natural talent beyond that of most people.~
@10480  = ~Child, that kind of stuff IS hard - for most people. But for you it is remarkably simple. You seem to have been born with... unique aptitudes. And I would like to help you make the most of them. I propose to take you on as my apprentice, to guide you and tutor you in the use of magic. I think that you could fairly easily, in time, be as skilled as I am.~
@10481  = ~Imoen, hear me: I am quite serious. You will have quarters here in the Ducal Palace. You will be trained as an agent of the Dukes of Baldur's Gate. You will come to do great works, but in your own way. Not necessarily running around in dungeons and mines. With the right guidance, I think you could do so much more.~
@10482  = ~But Imoen, this means your work here would starting now. I would ask that you stay here with me, and begin your studies, while your companions go on this mission for Duke Belt. What say you?~
@10483  = ~Then it is agreed. Imoen, let us begin immediately, I will help you familiarize yourself with the palace. <CHARNAME>, we shall see you again soon.~
@10484  = ~Uh... you wanna speak to me??~
@10485  = ~I mean, that kind of stuff isn't very hard. You're giving me too much credit.~
@10486  = ~What? That's, I couldn't... Say, you aren't joking, are you? Because, if so you are totally committing to the bit. I mean, where would I live and stuff?~
@10487  = ~Wow! <CHARNAME>, you hear that? Duke Liia thinks I have potential!~
@10488  = ~Of course, Imoen. I've always known you have potential.~
@10489  = ~Yes... she seems to have an angle. I just haven't figured out what it is, yet...~
@10490  = ~Yeah, but now someone important thinks so!~
@10491  = ~I, uh, geez. I'm not sure what to say. I think... I think I want to say yes? <CHARNAME>, I know you need me and all - you would be totally lost without me. But maybe not anymore? This trip seems pretty simple. Maybe you could handle this one on your own.~
@10492  = ~I gotta be honest, I kinda like the sound of staying here. Not that I haven't enjoyed tromping around the country with you but I'm kinda tired of it? The monsters, the undead, the murderous bozos... the dirt. So much dirt!~
@10493  = ~Liia thinks I could be helpful and powerful and all, but from here! I could eat hot food, wear nice things, sleep in a comfy bed. I have to tell you, I really miss that stuff. And you're working for the Dukes as well, now! So it's not like we can't see each other whenever we want to.~
@10494  = ~Well, Imoen, if that's what you want, I wouldn't tell you otherwise. I'm really happy for you to have such an opportunity. I think you absolutely deserve it.~
@10495  = ~Imoen, your job is to assist me. You can't leave now.~
@10496  = ~Really? Oh, thank you for being so understanding! This is really exciting! I promise I'll do really well, and when you get in trouble I'll say nice things about you! Because that's what friends do, right? You'll do the same for me... right?~
@10497  = ~What? Geez, I'm looking for a little support here! You know I'm not just here for your sake. I've been saving your butt time and again, whether you realize it or not. Not everything is about you! I'm sorry, but I just can't pass up this kind of opportunity. Liia seems really nice - probably nicer than you. Uh, no offense.~
@10498  = ~You can use my gear if you want! I won't need it here. I'll put it in my chest up on the third floor if you want to borrow any of it.~
@10499  = ~Heya! I'm studying with Liia. It's kinda boring, but really cool too!~
//
//
@10501  = ~The Hunt for Sarevok
Sarevok has been defeated once and for all. He had prepared some kind of ritual in an old temple of Bhaal, trapping me there and hoping to gain power from my death somehow. Thankfully it was he who died. The ritual must have affected him instead, because his body disintegrated in an obviously magical way. I do not know what to make of that. In any event, I should report what happened to Dukes Belt and Liia. Maybe now that Sarevok is gone, things on the Sword Coast can go back to normal.~
@10511  = ~And now comes the mosquito to the spider's den. I underestimated you, <CHARNAME>. You successfully toppled my plans. War was to come to Baldur's Gate - I would have been a tragic hero, as the city fell to conquerors. As the Amnish army poured in, there would have been murder on the grandest scale!~
@10512  = ~You are thrall to our father's dreams! I have not let myself be defined by him; you do not need to be driven by the pursuit of death!~
@10513  = ~Why? How could mass murder benefit you! You made yourself out to be the city's leader; if it fell, you would have been disgraced!~
@10514  = ~I appreciate what you accomplished, but why then throw it all away to be on the losing side of a war? You already achieved power in the Iron Throne, and then destroyed it from within. You actions don't add up.~
@10515  = ~~
@10516  = ~Fool! I do not do this out of reverence, or for some abstract principle! Our father was weak! Even with the power of a god, he perished! I have no interest in following his example. No - I do this for power!~
@10517  = ~Power? You had power, and lost it in your pursuit of mass murder. If you are not in it for the principle, then how would war empower you?~
@10518  = ~Your power has run out. We have pursued you to the last dark corner you could run to. Now I will finally be free of you.~
@10519  = ~~
@10520  = ~~
@10521  = ~You have no idea what this place is. We are directly under the gates to the inner city. Jergal's clergy were once lords of this land, using ritual death to fuel their power. I have prepared the old rites have been once again!- all of the deaths at the hands of Amnish invaders would have been magically captured, and funneled to a single point of focus - the residual spark of Bhaal that beats in my heart!~
@10522  = ~What could you hope to gain by resurrecting a dead god? All this to become - a high priest? Do you think he would favor you?~
@10523  = ~All this to resurrect your father? Were you so damaged growing up without him? Somehow I suspect he would not have been very paternal...~
@10524  = ~~
@10525  = ~Oh, I do not wish to restore Bhaal's power. He is long gone. All that remains is us, and what we do with his legacy. I know you have felt the hunger, the urge not just to end life, but to TAKE it! But, it is far too late for you.~
@10526  = ~The rituals in this place are still active - but now attuned to you! The doors are sealed - this will be your slaughterhouse. As you sputter your last breath I will absorb your divine soul! I will not be a god - not yet - but with twice Bhaal's power I will be unstoppable!~
@10527  = ~You'll be dead!~
@10528  = ~You know I will not let that happen. We have prevailed over your goons at every step - and we will prevail today.~
@10529  = ~~
@10530  = ~Yes, <PRO_BROTHERSISTER>! Bring your rage to bear, and we shall end this in a manner befitting our heritage! Face me! Face the new LORD OF MURDER! Angelo! Tazok! Reveal yourselves and let's finish this now!~
//
//
@10601  = ~The Hunt for Sarevok
Sarevok and his followers are defeated at long last, his murderous schemes fully unraveled. Your foster father, Gorion, has been avenged. For the first time since you left Candlekeep, you have the opportunity to reflect on the astonishing turns your life has taken.
Though you are fêted by the rulers of Baldur's Gate, a sense of unease plagues you. You can't help but hear whispers, hinting that you killed your half-brother not for the good of the city, but so you could usurp his place and his power. For the moment, however, your persecutors' voices are drowned out by an ever-growing number of others with more immediate concerns.
Every day, more refugees are driven from their homes by the followers of Caelar Argent and travel toward the city of Baldur's Gate. Many have stories of the Shining Lady's grace; all have tales of her followers' wrath.
Your thoughts are troubled. You wonder what effect Caelar's crusade will have on Baldur's Gate, little knowing how close at hand the answer is...~
@10602  = ~<CHARNAME>! We did not expect you so quickly. Did you find passage to the Undercity? Do you have information on Sarevok's whereabouts? I have asked Captain Gregson of the Flaming Fist to have a company of soldiers and battlemages prepared to apprehend him. Not as many as I would like - the Crusade is gathering strength in the north and most of our armed forces are assembling to march in that direction. Never mind that, though - tell us what you have learned.~
@10603  = ~Sarevok is dead. I trailed him to an old temple of Bhaal, where he had arranged some kind of magical trap. The entire place was glowing with some kind of energy. I could not escape.~
@10604  = ~It is Sarevok who has learned the hardest of lessons. He trapped me and thought he could best me, but he was very wrong. He and his last followers fell to my onslaught.~
@10605  = ~What! Are you- well obviously you survived. Tell us what happened.~
@10606  = ~We had no choice but to fight. It was that, or die. He had some kind of ritual planned, but in the end it came to naught. He and his associates fell, and his very body crumbled to nothing.~
@10607  = ~Sarevok was overconfident, and fell to my power. In the end there was nothing left of him.~
@10608  = ~What do you mean 'nothing?' Please tell me that you safeguarded his remains. Dead or not, we need to interrogate him. There is still the matter of the attack against Duke Silvershield, and several other loose threads.~
@10609  = ~This is a serious matter. We must know whether any remnants of his supporters may still threaten the city. The ranks of the crusade are swelling in the north, to the point where it may present an existential threat to nearby cities. We cannot have our attention divided between the threat without and a threat within.~
@10610  = ~Sarevok is dead and will trouble the city no more. The bodies of Tazok, Angelo, and another mage are still there. But Sarevok... he just disappeared in a swirl of glowing motes. Given where were, it may have had something to do with the ritual he had planned? It is hard to say. But he is truly dead, and beyond returning. I know it. In my bones.~
@10611  = ~What do you want me to say? He's gone. Good riddance.~
@10612  = ~This is unbelievable! How do we know any of that even happened? I have heard the reports - Sarevok was said to be immensely powerful. Are we to believe this... this upstart could have defeated Sarevok and his top lieutenants, in the heart of his of power? We cannot credit this story. For all we know they could have been working together the whole time! Sarevok may be running to meet with Caelar Argent, then to march against the city at the head of a wildling army!~
@10613  = ~Daddy, really, what are you talking about?~
@10614  = ~That seems unlikely. The circumstances would have to be pretty convoluted for that to be the case. If <CHARNAME> were- ~
@10615  = ~I am NOT interested in conjecture! I am interested in what can be proven! This has been a disaster for the city. Our iron was poisoned, our military readiness reduced, our trading costers brutally attacked, ONE of us was assassinated, however temporarily, and the other three were nearly killed as well. And <CHARNAME> has been tangled up in it from the beginning!~
@10616  = ~And he has still not answered for my murder. I tell you, it was no doppelganger. That would make no sense anyway; Sarevok left evidence connecting the murder to the Shadow Thieves, so why would the murderer not take the form of a Shadow Thief? I tell you, something about this stinks. I demand that <CHARNAME> submit to our custody until we can get to the bottom of it. <PRO_HESHE> should be subject to divination and forced interrogation.~
@10617  = ~Entar. I sympathize with what you went through, but I disagree about that course of action. I have had accounts from the Flaming Fist about <CHARNAME>'s performance rooting out Korlasz, working with our men to defeat her while showing mercy where appropriate.~
@10618  = ~Entar. I sympathize with what you went through, but I disagree about that course of action. I have had accounts from the Flaming Fist about <CHARNAME>'s performance rooting out Korlasz, working with our men to soundly defeat her and all of her followers.~
@10619  = ~The threat of the Crusade is too great not to use all of our resources. <CHARNAME> has failed to follow our instructions, but ultimately, the outcome is the one we desired: Sarevok is no more. We should focus on the real, very visible threat to our city, rather than imagined threats. And what better way for <CHARNAME> to prove <PRO_HISHER> loyalty and good faith than by putting <PRO_HISHER> skills to use on the field of battle, in the name of Baldur's Gate?~
@10620  = ~I do not know... since Sarevok's attack I have immersed myself in research about Bhaal's actions during the Time of Troubles, and the prophecies surrounding Sarevok and others of his ilk. Sarevok was far from alone; it is said there are scores of these... "Bhaal-spawned" individuals in the world. Prophecy holds that they will converge on the Sword Coast. Alaundo did not predict when it would happen, but what if Sarevok's actions are the spark that draws these beings to us, like moths to the proverbial flame, "with chaos in their wake?"~
@10621  = ~This crusade forming in the north - I doubt it is coincidental. Its leader, Caelar Argent... could she be like Sarevok? Her family is well-known, but who can say what may have happened, when gods are involved? What if the concerns inside our city and outside it are connected? I fear the peril faced by our city has not ended, but will only intensify.~
@10622  = ~<CHARNAME>, I would like to hear from you. Obviously we are not entirely happy with how your hunt for Sarevok resolved itself. Your coin is on edge at the moment. You would do well to demonstrate that you have the interests of Baldur's Gate at heart, and not some other agenda. So, what would you propose? Will you stay and prove your innocence to Duke Silvershield? Or will you prove yourself by helping the city to address the threat of Caelar Argent? I am afraid, under the circumstances, that there is no third option.~
@10623  = ~Before answering that, I feel it would be best if I tell you something. In Candlekeep, I found a letter from Gorion. Apparently when I was a baby, he took me from a temple of Bhaal, just after the Time of Troubles. He believes I am one of the children sired by the god - just like Sarevok. Gorion never hinted at such a thing before... evidently he wanted to shield me from the events of the prophecy. But I suppose it is who I am, and you should know that.~
@10624  = ~I have only ever worked for the good of Baldur's Gate. Let me continue that work. I have had enough of Sarevok's schemes and shapechangers. I will help you investigate this crusade, and if necessary, I will put a stop to it just as I put a stop to Sarevok.~
@10625  = ~In truth, I am not feeling very welcome in this city, and being here has become less and less pleasant. But this crusade sounds like an interesting challenge. And maybe this Caelar person has information about Sarevok and... his siblings. I will work for you, and go see about this threat in the north.~
@10626  = ~If someone or something out there is wearing my face, I need to know who, and why. I have no interest in this Caelar person, she sounds like a simple petty warlord. You will have to investigate the crusade without me, I am staying in the city.~
@10627  = ~Are you sure that is your choice? There will be no going back: we will have Gregson and the local constabulary look into this remaining doppelganger business. You will be working directly for the Grand Dukes of Baldur's Gate. You must commit to giving your full attention to any missions we give you.~
@10628  = ~Are you sure that is your choice? There will be no catching up: we will engage others to investigate Caelar, and soon enough the Flaming Fist will march north to confront her, without you. You will not have another chance to participate in that confrontation. Whatever is happening at Castle Dragonspear will not be your concern; your business will be to the south.~
@10629  = ~Oh my gods, dad. Have you noticed, I'M in this company? Ugh, this is so embarrassing!~
@10630  = ~You... what?? Are you all hearing this? <CHARNAME> is a chaos agent, just like Sarevok. Now more than ever, the Council must heed my concerns! Another Bhaal-child. And what of the others? Maybe it is a whole company of them! Who knows what danger they pose?~
@10631  = ~That is... unexpected. Though, from everything I now know, perhaps unsurprising. And you never knew, until recently? Fascinating. Whatever your parentage, you are clearly not cut from the same cloth as Sarevok. Your actions heretofore have aptly proven that. There are debates among sages about whether direct divine influence in a mortal's blood would overpower them, or whether their own soul can retain its independence. I suppose we are seeing this question play out, in real time. My own opinion is that mortal souls are wondrous and powerful things, that even gods cannot subsume. That is, of course, why the gods need mortal flocks. But that is just supposition. To have a true test case...~
@10632  = ~That is... unexpected. Though, from everything I now know, perhaps unsurprising.I am not sure how to feel about this revelation. I have noticed your tendency to put your concern for yourself above others. On its own, this is not a problem; heavens know many, many other people have similar tendencies! And whatever the shade of your moral fiber, you are clearly not cut from the same cloth as Sarevok. You are, as I say, balancing on a knife's edge at the moment. Your next move will be telling.~
@10633  = ~We thank you for your honesty. It strikes me that may be a particularly sensitive thing to admit, so I appreciate your openness. If anything, I think this helps your case, since you easily could have remained in silence. You are acting like a true ally, which is to your benefit. I suppose, now that we know about Sarevok and that the time mentioned in the prophecy is upon us, every foundling child will be suspect. Er, no offense, of course.~
@10634  = ~Ultimately, however, it changes little in the short term. I also would like to hear what you propose to do. Will you assist us in dealing with the threat of the crusade in the north? Or will you follow the last threads of Sarevok's scheming and find out the truth of Duke Entar's murder? (Though, I must say, this business of a murderer with your likeness has the whiff of a trap...)~
@10635  = ~Very well. You have so far proven your value to Baldur's Gate, and you may be an asset in dealing with Caelar Argent. She seems to be gathering an army, and in Dragonspear Castle, she has established a very dangerous base of operations. Ordinarily that would be cause for great concern; but Caelar is a noble paladin in the Order of the Aster! Her followers call themselves a crusade... but against what are they crusading? Too many things do not add up.~
@10636  = ~Very well. Our interests seem to be aligned, so we can at least trust you to that extent. We need information about Caelar Argent. She seems to be gathering an army, and in Dragonspear Castle, she has established a very dangerous base of operations. Ordinarily that would be cause for great concern; but Caelar is a noble paladin in the Order of the Aster! Her followers call themselves a crusade... but against what are they crusading? Too many things do not add up.~
@10637  = ~We are mustering an expeditionary force, to be led by Flaming Fist officers, to travel north and secure the Coast Way Crossing over the Boareskyr river. It is a vital junction for the city's trade and prosperity. Then the force will march to Dragonspear Castle and confront Caelar Argent. But we need to know more about her before parlaying with her.~
@10638  = ~This is something you can help us with. Apparently she has a cousin and former comrade-in-arms, who resides not far from here. His name is Dauston. He was an accomplished paladin, but reports had him in Beregost, in reduced circumstances, spending much time in taverns. We are not sure what happened to the man. Find Sir Dauston, talk to him, see if he can give us any useful information.~
@10639  = ~Well, what is it to be then? This is your chance to make a choice as to where your future lies: north toward Dragonspear, or here in the south. Choose well.~
@10640  = ~Yes, I am sure.~
@10641  = ~Wait, let me reconsider.~
@10642  = ~But first, we must let the people of the city know that order has been restored. They need to know that the villain is defeated, slain by a hero. Whether or not that is what you really are, the fact is you did stop Sarevok. The whispers about you have already started; it would be prudent to make sure the less kind ones do not become dominant. Come: you will be presented as the 'Hero of Baldur's Gate.'~
@10643  = ~~
@10644  = ~skipping sod, get to jail cut scene~
@10645  = ~Sarevok and his followers are defeated at long last, his murderous schemes fully unraveled. Your foster father, Gorion, has been avenged. For the first time since you left Candlekeep, you have the opportunity to reflect on the astonishing turns your life has taken.

Though you are fêted by the rulers of Baldur's Gate, a sense of unease plagues you. You can't help but hear whispers, hinting that you killed your half-brother not for the good of the city, but so you could usurp his place and his power. For the moment, however, your persecutors' voices are drowned out by an ever-growing number of others with more immediate concerns.

Every day, more refugees are driven from their homes by the followers of Caelar Argent and travel toward the city of Baldur's Gate. Many have stories of the Shining Lady's grace; all have tales of her followers' wrath.

Your thoughts are troubled. You wonder what effect Caelar's crusade will have on Baldur's Gate, little knowing how close at hand the answer is...~
@10646  = ~I would like some time to consider this decision. Please, I have been through much. I need to rest, and consider my path. Then I will return and inform you which path I will choose.~
@10647  = ~Very well, I suppose that is reasonable. Do not take too long though. There is much to do.~
@10648  = ~Very well. You will not be included in the expeditionary force to Dragonspear Castle.~ 
@10649  = ~You have returned. What is your decision?~
@10650  = ~The Hunt for Sarevok
Sarevok and his followers are defeated at long last, his murderous schemes fully unraveled. Your foster father, Gorion, has been avenged. With the exception of your friend Imoen, those who helped you thwart your half-brother's schemes drift away from you, returning to their lives. For the first time since you left Candlekeep, you have the opportunity to reflect on the astonishing turns your life has taken.
Nevertheless a sense of unease still plagues you. Unease about deaths that, somehow, you know do not fit with the others you have seen. Somewhere out there, someone walks the city wearing your face. Is it really a remnant of Sarevok's plans? Or something else?
Refugees driven from their homes by the servants of Caelar Argent are heading toward the city. Chaos and desperation are rising in Baldur's Gate. But some small voice is telling you that they are not your concern. You must find out why.~
@10651  = ~The forces of Baldur's Gate are mustering as we speak. We will provide you with quarters here in the palace until it is time to leave. Rest well, we will speak again in the morning.~
@10652  = ~Now then, go to Beregost. Find Dauston, learn what you can. It will take some time for the Flaming Fist to assemble our forces and march north; so this is not a matter of utmost urgency. If you have any other business to complete outside the city, this would be a good time to do so. Once you have spoken to Sir Dauston, report back her to us. Understood? Good luck.~
@10653  = ~Have you found sir dauston yet? Have you learned anything about Caelar Argent?~
@10654  = ~Not yet.~
@10655  = ~~
@10671  = ~Thank you for sending Sir Dauston to us. Please accept my apologies - we did not expect for your mission to involve violence. I would like to hear your take on the man, but then we will move on to the next phase of this operation. What we will ask of you concerns you alone - not your companions. Are you prepared to move forward? There will be no going back; if you have any outstanding business you can go complete it, and return to me when you are ready to move on. Do you understand?~
@10672  = ~I am ready to move on. Really ready. I get it.~
@10673  = ~Let us delay this conversation then, while I finish up my business. I will return.~
@10674  = ~Very well. On our end we will continue to debrief Sir Dauston, but for the moment he will be secured in a safe location, protected from any further actions by agents of Caelar Argent. Tell me, what do you think of what he told you about her?~
@10675  = ~He said she was descended from a solar. That would make her an aasimar.~
@10676  = ~Yes. Aasimar are not unheard of, but with ancestry from a solar... that is exceedingly rare. Solars are practically gods in their own right. Stories of a solar interacting with mortals at all are exceedingly rare.~
@10677  = ~Sir Dauston said something about Caelar reenacting her ancestor's actions. Do you know what that could mean?~
@10678  = ~No... it would of course depend on who that ancestor was. And it may have been so long ago that we would have no knowledge of the events. On the other hand, this at least sheds some light on why Caelar chooses to call her war effort a "crusade."~
@10679  = ~Could her cause truly be righteous? Is our oppositional stance the correct response? If she means well, why choose a stronghold over a portal to the Nine Hells? Could she be protecting it from some outside incursion? There are so many unanswered questions!~
@10680  = ~You are trying to find logic in her actions. But Sir Dauston seemed to think that Caelar is delusional.~
@10681  = ~That may well be the case. But in a way, it would be a much more concerning prospect. To have her power, her influence, an army at her back... if she has lost touch with reality, this crusade could be incredibly destructive. Reports tell us that many innocents have already suffered in the area under her sway. As here sphere of influence expands, such devastation would grow with it.~
@10682  = ~Of course Sir Dauston himself may not be entirely reliable. His own mind is clearly touched, and thick with drink. I prefer not to assume the worst about Caelar.~
@10683  = ~Ultimately, we must find out the truth. Preparations for the Flaming Fist's expedition are almost complete. We have been in touch with officials from Waterdeep and Daggerford. Our troops will rendezvous with theirs, and together we will confront the crusade.~
@10684  = ~We would like you to join the Flaming Fist, and travel with them to Dragonspear Castle. I know you are not a soldier, and I do not expect you to be in the army's command structure. But the roads are dangerous, doubly so as the effects of the Crusade spread south. The forces will undoubtedly encounter situations that can best be handled by adventurers. And beyond that, you are a celebrity, a hero of the city, the slayer of Sarevok. You averted a war once; it would do people well to think that it might be averted again.~
@10685  = ~I would be honored to travel to Dragonspear Castle with the Flaming Fist, to represent the interests of Baldur's Gate.~
@10686  = ~Caelar's agent had a particular interest in me. I need to find out why. If that means traveling alongside your little army, so be it.~
@10687  = ~I will not commit to such a voyage. I have no interest in serving in military campaigns, and Dragonspear Castle is no concern of mine. Caelar is raising an army; you have your army. You can have your little war, but I will not take part in it.~
@10688  = ~Wonderful. I am glad to hear you will continue to serve our city, and I am certain that Captain Corwin and Corporal Bence will be equally happy. For the moment, I suggest you rest while the Flaming Fist make final preparations to move out.~
@10689  = ~Very well, I will do that.~
@10690  = ~Very well, no one will force you. One way or another, you have earned the right to make such decisions for yourself. Your destiny is your own, surely.~
@10691  = ~You found Caelar's cousin! Good job. Things have been progressing here. Belt can talk to you about next steps.~
